WEBVTT

00:05.740 --> 00:09.241
<i> WOMAN:</i>
<i> (SCREAMING)</i>
<i> OH MY GOD! NO!</i>

00:09.243 --> 00:10.376
<i> NOOOOO!</i>

00:12.346 --> 00:14.747
<i> OH MY GOD, MY BABY!</i>
<i> MY BABY!</i>

00:16.417 --> 00:17.716
<i> (BABY CRIES)</i>

00:21.355 --> 00:22.788
(SOUNDS MILES AWAY)
ED!

00:22.790 --> 00:24.390
(BREATHING HARD)

00:26.360 --> 00:28.460
(SIREN CHIRPS,
SLIGHTLY ECHOING)

00:28.462 --> 00:30.195
<i> WOMAN:</i>
<i> (SHRIEKING)</i>
<i> OH MY GOD! OH MY GOD!</i>

00:30.197 --> 00:32.364
(WEEPING)

00:32.366 --> 00:36.335
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENED UP THERE, ED?</i>

00:36.337 --> 00:38.670
<i> EDDIE!</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENED UP THERE?</i>

00:38.672 --> 00:42.441
(ROARING INCREASES
IN ED'S EARS)

00:48.182 --> 00:49.548
DR. BELL:
(INTO PHONE)
...JUST ABOUT.

00:49.550 --> 00:52.084
YOU WANT ME TO PICK UP ANYTHING
ON THE WAY HOME?

00:52.086 --> 00:53.819
SURE.
RED OR WHITE?

00:54.755 --> 00:56.455
(LAUGHS)

00:56.457 --> 00:58.724
SOMETHING "FULL-BODIED
AND JUICY."

00:58.726 --> 01:01.160
HONEY, I STILL HAVE MY FREUD
TEXTBOOKS FROM MED SCHOOL,

01:01.162 --> 01:03.228
DON'T MAKE ME USE 'EM.

01:03.230 --> 01:04.430
RIGHT NOW?

01:04.432 --> 01:07.833
<i> RADIO STREAM:</i>
<i> SHOOTING TOOK PLACE</i>
<i> ON THE CENTER ISLAND FERRY</i>

01:07.835 --> 01:09.501
<i> JUST OVER AN HOUR AGO.</i>

01:09.503 --> 01:11.103
<i> SRU WERE ON SCENE</i>

01:11.105 --> 01:13.505
<i> AND THE SPECIAL</i>
<i> INVESTIGATIONS UNIT CONFIRMS</i>

01:13.507 --> 01:15.808
<i> THERE HAS BEEN</i>
<i> A CIVILIAN FATALITY.</i>

01:15.810 --> 01:17.810
DR. BELL:
(CLICKING IT OFF)
I DON'T KNOW.

01:17.812 --> 01:20.746
WELL, NO, I COULDN'T TELL YOU
EVEN IF HE WAS.

01:20.748 --> 01:22.392
THAT-THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

01:22.393 --> 01:24.037
YOU MAKE A GREAT DINNER
EVERY NIGHT.

01:24.038 --> 01:25.682
YOU CAN'T BRIBE ME THAT WAY.
(KNOCK AT THE DOOR)

01:25.686 --> 01:26.819
I WILL.

01:28.389 --> 01:29.655
I LOVE YOU TOO.
(PHONE BEEPS OFF)

01:31.659 --> 01:33.525
(CONFUSED)
ED!
HEY!

01:33.527 --> 01:35.427
DID WE... I DIDN'T FORGET
A SESSION, DID I?

01:35.429 --> 01:36.862
NO, NO. I JUST WANTED
TO DROP OFF THE BOOKS

01:36.864 --> 01:38.597
AND THE JOURNAL AND STUFF
YOU LENT ME.

01:38.599 --> 01:40.332
ARE YOU DONE
WITH THEM?

01:40.334 --> 01:41.633
ACTUALLY, I'M DONE
WITH THE SESSIONS

01:41.635 --> 01:42.668
AND THE THERAPY.

01:42.670 --> 01:44.403
I JUST WANTED
TO LET YOU KNOW.

01:44.405 --> 01:46.338
OKAY. CAN YOU COME IN
FOR A SEC?

01:46.340 --> 01:48.107
YEAH.
<i>CAN YOU SHUT</i>
<i>THE DOOR?</i>

01:48.109 --> 01:49.441
SURE.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.509
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE BUSY,
SO...

01:50.511 --> 01:52.311
NO, IT'S FINE.

01:52.313 --> 01:53.879
<i> I JUST NEED THROUGH</i>
<i> A FEW THINGS</i>

01:53.881 --> 01:55.681
TO WRAP UP OUR WORK.

01:56.550 --> 01:58.617
DO YOU HAVE A SEC?
YEAH.

01:59.753 --> 02:01.553
OKAY, AND YOU STARTED COMING
HERE, WHEN WAS THAT?

02:01.555 --> 02:03.622
TWO MONTHS - TWO MONTHS,
ONE WEEK, FIVE DAYS.

02:05.326 --> 02:07.526
THAT'S RIGHT.
(LAUGHS)

02:07.528 --> 02:10.462
YOU WANTED TO TALK ABOUT SOME
SPECIFIC ISSUES AROUND A CASE,

02:10.464 --> 02:12.197
"MAY DALTON."

02:12.199 --> 02:13.632
SHAME, WE NEVER GOT AROUND
TO TALKING ABOUT THAT.

02:13.634 --> 02:15.134
OH, THAT'S OKAY.

02:15.136 --> 02:16.602
LOOK,
YOU HAVE BEEN GREAT.

02:16.604 --> 02:18.470
YOU'VE GIVEN ME A LOT OF STUFF
TO THINK ABOUT,

02:18.472 --> 02:19.605
AND I JUST WANTED
TO SAY THANKS.

02:19.607 --> 02:21.473
I APPRECIATE THAT.

02:21.475 --> 02:22.691
I'M WONDERING, THOUGH,

02:22.692 --> 02:23.908
WHY YOU FEEL LIKE
YOU'RE DONE WITH THERAPY?

02:23.911 --> 02:25.677
UH...

02:25.679 --> 02:29.581
NO OFFENSE,
IT'S JUST NOT FOR ME.

02:29.583 --> 02:30.449
SO I'M NOT THAT GREAT,
HUH?

02:30.451 --> 02:31.450
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

02:31.452 --> 02:33.552
YOU KINDA JUST DID.

02:34.488 --> 02:35.838
BUT - CAN I ASK,

02:35.839 --> 02:37.189
WE DIDN'T HAVE A SESSION BOOKED
TILL NEXT WEEK -

02:37.191 --> 02:38.924
WHY DIDN'T JUST DROP
THE STUFF OFF THEN?

02:38.925 --> 02:40.658
ED:
NO, I JUST, I...
I HATE WHEN PEOPLE BORROW STUFF

02:40.661 --> 02:42.561
AND DON'T RETURN 'EM,
SO...

02:42.563 --> 02:44.630
THIS WOULDN'T HAVE ANYTHING
TO DO WITH TODAY, WOULD IT?

02:44.632 --> 02:47.199
CENTER ISLAND FERRY?

02:47.201 --> 02:48.367
I CAN'T TALK ABOUT THAT.

02:48.369 --> 02:49.601
YOU CAN TALK ABOUT
ANYTHING HERE, ED -

02:49.603 --> 02:51.470
YOU KNOW THAT -
IF YOU WANT TO.

02:51.472 --> 02:52.704
WHATEVER HAPPENED TODAY,

02:52.706 --> 02:53.805
IT'S GOT NOTHING TO DO
WITH THAT,

02:53.807 --> 02:55.240
IT'S NOT WHY I'M DONE.

02:55.242 --> 02:57.543
OKAY.

02:57.545 --> 03:00.279
LOOK, YOU'VE ALREADY PAID
FOR THIS WEEK'S SESSION.

03:00.281 --> 03:02.331
AND I LIKE YOU, ED,

03:02.332 --> 03:04.382
BUT I'M STILL GONNA
CHARGE YOU FOR IT.

03:04.385 --> 03:05.651
YOU'RE HERE ANYWAY,

03:05.652 --> 03:06.918
<i> WHY DON'T YOU JUST TELL ME</i>
<i> ABOUT YOUR DAY.</i>

03:09.423 --> 03:11.857
YOU SURE THERE'S, UH,
NO PLACE YOU HAVE TO BE?

03:11.859 --> 03:14.326
I'M RIGHT WHERE
I NEED TO BE.

03:15.596 --> 03:16.795
OKAY.

03:16.797 --> 03:18.797
THE DAY STARTED NORMAL.

03:18.799 --> 03:21.200
UP EARLY, OUT EARLY.
JUST THE WAY I LIKE IT.

03:21.202 --> 03:22.734
(ALARM CLOCK BLARES)

03:25.606 --> 03:27.506
DON'T YOU LOOK NICE...

03:27.507 --> 03:29.407
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> HOW'S THE FAMILY?</i>
<i> SOPHIE, ISABELLE...</i>

03:29.410 --> 03:30.509
<i> ED:</i>
<i> GOOD.</i>

03:31.445 --> 03:33.212
<i> DR. BELL</i>
<i> HOW ABOUT CLARK?</i>

03:33.214 --> 03:34.279
CUTIE...

03:36.917 --> 03:38.528
JUST YOU HAD MENTIONED

03:38.529 --> 03:40.140
YOU GUYS WERE HAVING
SOME ISSUES COMMUNICATING.

03:40.141 --> 03:41.752
NO, HE'S GOOD. WE'RE ALL GOOD.
WE'RE ALL GOOD.

03:41.755 --> 03:43.589
WORK WAS-
"GOOD?"

03:43.591 --> 03:45.657
(LAUGHS) IT WAS.

03:47.695 --> 03:49.228
ED:
ALL RIGHT!

03:49.230 --> 03:51.363
ALL RIGHT, NOW,
I LOVE TODAY.

03:51.365 --> 03:53.398
DO YOU KNOW WHY
I LOVE TODAY?

03:53.400 --> 03:54.683
SPIKE:
WHATEVER IT IS,

03:54.684 --> 03:55.967
I'M GUESSING IT MEANS
WHY WE WON'T LOVE TODAY.

03:55.970 --> 03:57.603
THAT'S RIGHT!
TODAY IS DRILL DAY -

03:57.605 --> 03:59.771
RACES, WEIGHTS,
PUNISHING PHYSICAL ACTIVITY.

03:59.773 --> 04:01.540
WHAT'S NOT TO LOVE?

04:01.542 --> 04:03.108
(LAUGHS) WOW.

04:03.109 --> 04:04.675
AND THEY HAVEN'T FOUND A WAY
TO ACCIDENTALLY SHOOT YOU YET?

04:04.678 --> 04:06.245
(LAUGHS)

04:06.246 --> 04:07.813
WELL, THERE'S A REASON WHY
WE'RE THE BEST TEAM IN THE CITY.

04:07.815 --> 04:09.815
TRUST ME,
THEY LOVE IT.

04:10.951 --> 04:12.384
ANYWAY,
IT DIDN'T MATTER.

04:12.386 --> 04:13.619
(KLAXON BLARES)
WINNIE:
HOT CALL, TEAM ONE.

04:13.621 --> 04:15.520
<i> 911 CALL,</i>
<i> FIREARMS INVOLVED.</i>

04:15.522 --> 04:17.389
SPIKE:
SAVED BY THE WINNIE!

04:17.391 --> 04:19.858
WINNIE:
MULTIPLE CALLERS REPORT
SINGLE WHITE MALE...

04:19.860 --> 04:21.593
ED:
WHITE MALE, 30'S,
DOWNTOWN AREA,

04:21.595 --> 04:23.462
HAD A DUFFEL BAG
AND FIREARM.

04:23.464 --> 04:25.697
YOU HEAR YOURSELF,
RIGHT?

04:25.699 --> 04:26.898
<i> YOU TALK TO ME LIKE</i>
<i> I'M YOUR SERGEANT,</i>

04:26.900 --> 04:28.834
OR THE SPECIAL
INVESTIGATIONS UNIT.

04:28.836 --> 04:30.002
I DON'T NEED
AN OFFICIAL REPORT.

04:30.004 --> 04:31.670
JUST TRY TELLING ME
LIKE UH...

04:31.672 --> 04:33.038
I'M A FRIEND,
OR ANOTHER COP.

04:33.040 --> 04:34.439
BUT YOU'RE NOT A COP.

04:34.441 --> 04:35.574
I MEAN, I'M SORRY,
BUT YOU'RE NOT.

04:35.576 --> 04:36.708
NO. I'M NOT.

04:36.710 --> 04:38.310
BUT I KNOW A BIT
ABOUT THE JOB.

04:38.312 --> 04:39.711
REALLY.

04:39.713 --> 04:40.912
WELL, HOW?

04:41.849 --> 04:44.683
JUST TRY...TELLING ME
THE STORY

04:44.685 --> 04:46.885
HOWEVER IT FEELS BEST.

04:48.856 --> 04:51.556
WE WERE UNSURE
WHERE THE SUBJECT WAS

04:51.558 --> 04:52.758
IN THE DOWNTOWN AREA.

04:52.760 --> 04:55.294
(SIRENS WAIL,
TIRES SQUEAL)

04:56.530 --> 04:57.963
ED:
SPIKE, TRAFFIC CAMS?

04:57.964 --> 04:59.397
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> SENDING YOU</i>
<i> WHAT WE'VE GOT SO FAR.</i>

04:59.398 --> 05:00.831
LOOKS LIKE HE'S HEADING SOUTH
ON BATHURST,

05:00.834 --> 05:02.634
<i> PAST LAKESHORE.</i>

05:02.636 --> 05:04.069
(TABLET BEEPS)

05:04.071 --> 05:05.704
LOOKS BIGGER THAN
A SIDEARM TO ME.

05:05.706 --> 05:06.938
COULD BE A SAWED-OFF
SHOTGUN.

05:06.940 --> 05:08.573
HE'S CARRYING IT
OUT IN PUBLIC?

05:08.575 --> 05:09.675
<i> ED:</i>
<i> AND WHATEVER'S IN THAT BAG.</i>

05:09.677 --> 05:10.759
GUYS, WHAT DO WE GOT
DOWN THERE -

05:10.760 --> 05:11.842
<i> PARKS, CONSTRUCTION YARDS,</i>
<i> WHAT?</i>

05:11.845 --> 05:13.412
HARBOURFRONT.

05:13.413 --> 05:14.980
<i> ED:</i>
<i> OKAY, TEAM, HARBOURFRONT.</i>

05:14.981 --> 05:16.548
NO LIGHTS, NO SIRENS;
LET'S NOT SPOOK OUR SUBJECT.

05:16.550 --> 05:19.685
<i> SPIKE, LOOK FOR HIM ON</i>
<i> HARBOURFRONT CCTV FOOTAGE.</i>

05:19.687 --> 05:21.386
PARKER:
GUY'S CARRYING A WEAPON
IN PLAIN VIEW.

05:21.388 --> 05:22.754
WE MIGHT BE LOOKING
AT HEIGHTENED EMOTION,

05:22.756 --> 05:25.724
AND DESIRE TO PROVOKE
CONFRONTATION.

05:25.726 --> 05:27.426
SPIKE:
GUYS... (TABLET BEEPS)

05:27.428 --> 05:29.995
<i> HE'S GETTING ON</i>
<i> THE CENTER ISLAND FERRY.</i>

05:29.997 --> 05:31.697
<i> HIS WEAPON'S CONCEALED.</i>

05:31.699 --> 05:33.565
ED:
WE CAN'T LET THAT BOAT
GET OUT ON OPEN WATER.

05:33.567 --> 05:34.800
SPIKE:
NO, THE FOOTAGE IS FROM
FOUR MINUTES AGO.

05:34.802 --> 05:36.085
THE BOAT'S ALREADY LEFT.

05:36.086 --> 05:37.369
HE STARTS SHOOTING,
IT'S FISH IN A BARREL.

05:37.371 --> 05:38.470
WE'LL HAVE NO WAY
TO STOP HIM.

05:38.472 --> 05:40.072
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> WE GET A MARINE CRUISER,</i>

05:40.073 --> 05:41.673
WE CAN BOARD FROM THE PORT SIDE
EMERGENCY LADDER.

05:41.675 --> 05:43.058
JULES:
THEN YOU LOSE THE ELEMENT
OF SURPRISE.

05:43.059 --> 05:44.442
WE COULD CALL THE BOAT BACK
TO THE TERMINAL,

05:44.445 --> 05:45.703
AND RUSH IT
WHEN IT DOCKS?

05:45.704 --> 05:46.962
ED:
THERE'S TOO MANY PEOPLE,
IT'S UNCONTROLLED.

05:46.963 --> 05:48.221
WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S IN THAT BAG;

05:48.222 --> 05:49.480
IF HE'S GOT A BOMB,
WEAPONS, WHAT.

05:49.483 --> 05:50.849
ISN'T THERE ANOTHER
OLD MARINE TERMINAL,

05:50.851 --> 05:52.351
DOWN BELOW LAKESHORE?

05:52.353 --> 05:53.819
THEY STILL GOT A DOCK,
TOTALLY ABANDONED.

05:53.821 --> 05:55.787
WE'D HAVE COMPLETE CONTROL.
GOOD THINKING, LEAH.

05:55.789 --> 05:57.055
ALL RIGHT, EDDIE,
YOU GET EYES IN ON THE BOAT,

05:57.057 --> 05:59.958
I'LL CO-ORDINATE
WITH THE PORT AUTHORITY.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.693
<i> PORT AUTHORITY:</i>
<i> WE'LL ANNOUNCE </i>
<i> AN EMERGENCY EVACUATION.</i>

06:01.695 --> 06:03.862
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> NO, NO. DON'T MAKE IT SOUND</i>
<i> LIKE AN EMERGENCY.</i>

06:03.864 --> 06:05.347
JUST HAVE THE CAPTAIN ANNOUNCE

06:05.348 --> 06:06.831
THAT THEY HAVE TO MAKE
A LAST MINUTE STOP

06:06.834 --> 06:08.600
<i> AND THEY'LL BE</i>
<i> ON THEIR WAY SOON.</i>

06:10.037 --> 06:11.770
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> THAT MUST BE HARD...</i>

06:11.772 --> 06:13.405
RUSHING TO A SCENE,

06:13.407 --> 06:15.040
<i> NOT KNOWING</i>
<i> WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO FACE.</i>

06:15.042 --> 06:17.776
I'D FIND THAT HARD.
SCARY, EVEN.

06:17.778 --> 06:21.380
WELL, YOU HOPE FOR THE BEST,
PLAN FOR THE WORST.

06:21.382 --> 06:23.249
(FERRY HORN BELLOWS)

06:23.250 --> 06:25.117
<i> FERRY CAPTAIN: (OVER SPEAKERS</i>
<i> WE ARE DOCKING TEMPORARILY</i>
<i> TO ADDRESS A MINOR REPAIR.</i>

06:25.119 --> 06:26.618
<i> THANK YOU FOR YOUR PATIENCE.</i>

06:26.620 --> 06:28.086
SAM:
GOOD VISUAL ON THE FERRY.

06:28.088 --> 06:29.788
<i> ED:</i>
<i> NO JOY ON THE SUBJECT.</i>

06:29.790 --> 06:31.556
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> EDDIE, WE'RE HOLDING OFF</i>
<i> ON THE GANGPLANK -</i>

06:31.558 --> 06:33.133
NO ONE ON OR OFF

06:33.134 --> 06:34.709
UNTIL WE KNOW WHAT
WE'RE DEALING WITH.

06:34.710 --> 06:36.285
<i> FERRY CAPTAIN:</i>
<i> I REPEAT: WE ARE DOCKING</i>
<i> TEMPORARILY</i>

06:36.286 --> 06:37.861
<i> TO ADDRESS A MINOR REPAIR.</i>
<i> THANK YOU FOR YOUR PATIENCE.</i>

06:37.865 --> 06:39.097
HE MUST BE INSIDE.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.701
<i> ED:</i>
<i> OKAY, HOLD ON.</i>
<i> WE GOT A MIDDLE-AGED MAN HERE,</i>

06:42.703 --> 06:44.870
<i> HE'S CARRYING A DUFFEL BAG.</i>

06:44.872 --> 06:46.872
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> CHECK HIS RIGHT ARM -</i>
<i> HE'S HIDING SOMETHING.</i>

06:50.511 --> 06:51.843
HE'S TALKING.

06:51.845 --> 06:53.295
TO WHO?

06:53.296 --> 06:54.746
ED:
I DON'T KNOW.
HE'S GOT NO PHONE. HE'S ALONE.

06:54.747 --> 06:56.197
HE'S GOT NO HEADSET.

06:56.198 --> 06:57.648
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> HE'S ACTING ERRATIC.</i>
<i> HE'S REACHING FOR THE BAG!</i>

06:57.651 --> 06:58.550
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHAT'S HE GOT IN THERE, EDDIE?</i>

07:02.689 --> 07:03.789
(BREATHING HARD)

07:03.791 --> 07:04.856
IT'S A BABY.

07:06.593 --> 07:16.701
¶¶¶

07:16.703 --> 07:21.773
¶¶¶

07:21.775 --> 07:34.019
¶¶¶

07:47.000 --> 07:48.733
A BABY, SAY AGAIN?

07:48.735 --> 07:53.104
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> AFFIRMATIVE.</i>
<i> SUBJECT HAS A BABY IN HIS BAG.</i>

07:59.613 --> 08:01.012
WHAT'S HE DOING?

08:04.785 --> 08:06.084
OKAY, WE LOST HIM.
HE'S GONE INSIDE, BOSS.

08:06.086 --> 08:08.820
I'M COMING DOWN
FOR ACTION PLAN.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.522
<i> OFFICER BRADDOCK REMAINED</i>
<i> IN POSITION</i>

08:10.524 --> 08:11.573
<i> TO COVER THE BOAT</i>

08:11.574 --> 08:12.623
<i> WHILE THE REST OF THE TEAM</i>
<i> AND MYSELF</i>

08:12.626 --> 08:14.059
<i> FORMED AN ACTION PLAN.</i>

08:14.061 --> 08:15.694
<i> THE PRIORITIES WERE:</i>
<i> SAVE THE INFANT,</i>

08:15.696 --> 08:17.162
<i> EVACUATE THE PASSENGERS,</i>

08:17.164 --> 08:19.030
<i> REMOVE THE SUBJECT</i>
<i> AS A THREAT.</i>

08:19.032 --> 08:20.265
WHAT WAS THAT LIKE?

08:20.267 --> 08:22.133
"LIKE?"

08:22.135 --> 08:23.468
THAT'S MY JOB.

08:23.469 --> 08:24.802
WE GET TWO OR THREE EDP CALLS
A WEEK -

08:24.805 --> 08:26.738
THAT'S "EMOTIONALLY
DISTURBED PERSON."

08:26.740 --> 08:29.241
I KNOW WHAT AN EDP IS;
THAT'S MY JOB.

08:29.243 --> 08:31.142
<i> I'M JUST WONDERING</i>
<i> WHAT IT'S LIKE TO BE THERE,</i>

08:31.144 --> 08:32.611
KNOWING THAT A LIFE'S
IN DANGER.

08:32.613 --> 08:35.547
KNOWING THAT...
IT'S UP TO YOU.

08:35.549 --> 08:37.516
YOU MEAN
"HOW DID IT FEEL?"

08:37.518 --> 08:38.817
WOULD I ASK SOMETHING
LIKE THAT?

08:38.819 --> 08:40.051
YOU JUST DID.

08:40.053 --> 08:42.687
(LAUGHS)
THAT'S TRUE.

08:45.058 --> 08:46.691
IT FELT GOOD.

08:46.693 --> 08:49.961
<i> BECAUSE I KNEW THAT WE WERE</i>
<i> THE BEST CHANCE THAT BABY -</i>

08:49.962 --> 08:53.230
AND THOSE PEOPLE -
HAD OF GETTING OUT ALIVE.

08:53.233 --> 08:55.600
BECAUSE OF MY TEAM.

08:55.602 --> 08:58.136
<i> THEY'RE FAST, THEY ARE SMART,</i>
<i> AND THEY'RE BRAVE.</i>

08:58.138 --> 09:00.171
<i> THEY'D GIVE THEIR LIVES</i>
<i> FOR EACH OTHER,</i>

09:00.173 --> 09:02.307
<i> THE PUBLIC, FOR ME.</i>

09:04.211 --> 09:06.645
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> AND YOUR SERGEANT?</i>

09:06.646 --> 09:09.080
<i> ED:</i>
<i> AND GREG HE'S A...</i>
<i> HE'S AT A WHOLE OTHER LEVEL.</i>

09:09.082 --> 09:11.049
<i> I MEAN,</i>
<i> NOBODY KNOWS PEOPLE BETTER -</i>

09:11.051 --> 09:12.884
<i> HOW THEY THINK,</i>
<i> WHAT THEY'LL DO.</i>

09:12.886 --> 09:14.185
HE WROTE THE BOOK,
HUH?

09:16.023 --> 09:17.156
HE IS THE BOOK.

09:17.157 --> 09:18.290
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> BOSS, I GOT AN AMBER ALERT</i>
<i> HERE,</i>

09:18.292 --> 09:19.925
<i> CAME OUT ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.</i>

09:19.927 --> 09:22.160
"KATHERINE THOMPSON,"
5-MONTH-OLD INFANT.

09:22.162 --> 09:23.562
OKAY, WINNIE,
LET'S PUT A CALL OUT TO THE-

09:23.564 --> 09:24.930
THE MOTHER?
I'M PATCHING HER THROUGH.

09:24.932 --> 09:26.798
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> NICE WORK, WINNIE.</i>

09:26.800 --> 09:28.533
MRS. THOMPSON?

09:28.534 --> 09:30.267
I'VE GOT SERGEANT GREG PARKER
ON THE LINE.

09:30.268 --> 09:32.001
MARIA THOMPSON:
OH MY GOD, WHERE'S MY BABY!
DO YOU HAVE MY BABY?!

09:32.005 --> 09:33.872
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> MRS. THOMPSON,</i>
<i> MY NAME IS GREG.</i>

09:33.874 --> 09:35.640
NOW, I CAN'T IMAGINE
WHAT YOU'RE FEELING RIGHT NOW,

09:35.642 --> 09:38.043
BUT I NEED YOU TO HELP ME
WITH SOMETHING, PLEASE.

09:38.045 --> 09:41.246
<i> ED:</i>
<i> NOW, YOU GET WHY HE DID THAT,</i>
<i> RIGHT?</i>

09:41.248 --> 09:43.715
TERRIFIED WOMAN,
OUT OF CONTROL.

09:43.717 --> 09:44.916
INSTEAD OF ASKING
ABOUT THE BABY -

09:44.918 --> 09:46.284
THE SOURCE OF HER FEAR -

09:46.286 --> 09:48.053
HE ASKS FOR A FAVOUR,

09:48.055 --> 09:50.789
GIVING HER
SOME CONTROL BACK.

09:50.791 --> 09:52.290
DID I PASS?

09:52.292 --> 09:53.925
HMM...

09:53.927 --> 09:55.193
WE NEEDED TO FIGURE OUT
A CONNECTION

09:55.195 --> 09:57.228
BETWEEN THE SUBJECT
AND THE BABY.

09:57.230 --> 09:59.731
PARKER:
SHE'S WITH A MAN,
IN HIS THIRTIES, BROWN HAIR...

09:59.733 --> 10:01.266
<i> MARIA:</i>
<i>IT WAS JUST HER AND ME ALL DAY.</i>

10:01.268 --> 10:02.784
SHE DOESN'T SLEEP SO WELL,

10:02.785 --> 10:04.301
SO ANYTIME SHE DOZES,
I PUT HER IN HER ROOM, ALONE.

10:04.304 --> 10:06.071
I OPENED THE WINDOW.

10:06.073 --> 10:07.272
<i> (TEARING UP)</i>
<i> I JUST DID IT FOR THE AIR.</i>

10:07.274 --> 10:09.307
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> BEST THING FOR A LITTLE ONE.</i>

10:09.309 --> 10:12.143
BUT WHO WOULD HAVE ACCESS
TO THAT WINDOW?

10:12.145 --> 10:14.646
MARIA:
I'M ON THE FIFTH FLOOR,
IT LEADS INTO A FIRE ESCAPE.

10:14.648 --> 10:16.147
SOMEONE COULD HAVE COME UP,
IT COULD-

10:16.149 --> 10:17.699
I DON'T KNOW,
I DON'T KNOW -

10:17.700 --> 10:19.250
IT COULD BE ANYONE,
I DON'T KNOW!

10:19.252 --> 10:21.219
ASK IF SHE KNOWS ANYBODY
WHO PLAYS PIANO.

10:21.221 --> 10:23.254
ANYBODY YOU KNOW PLAY PIANO,
MARIA?

10:23.256 --> 10:24.823
MARIA:
(FREEZES)

10:25.759 --> 10:26.758
HAROLD.

10:26.760 --> 10:28.810
HAROLD.
WHO'S THAT?

10:28.811 --> 10:30.861
<i> MARIA:</i>
<i> MY NEIGHBOUR.</i>
<i> HAROLD BEAMER, I THINK.</i>

10:30.864 --> 10:32.697
HE PLAYS PIANO ALL DAY
AND NIGHT.

10:32.699 --> 10:34.216
<i> SOMETIMES HE WAKES UP KATIE,</i>

10:34.217 --> 10:35.734
<i> BUT HE ALWAYS STOPS</i>
<i> WHEN I ASK HIM TO. </i>

10:35.736 --> 10:37.486
HE'S NICE,
HE'S NICE...

10:37.487 --> 10:39.237
EVEN IF HE'S A BIT...
WELL, CRAZY.

10:39.239 --> 10:40.872
CAN YOU EVEN SAY "CRAZY"
THESE DAYS?

10:40.874 --> 10:42.874
ED:
SAM, MEET US DOWN BELOW.
WE'LL COVER ONBOARD.

10:42.876 --> 10:44.275
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> COPY THAT.</i>
<i> ON MY WAY.</i>

10:46.179 --> 10:47.779
SPIKE:
RIGHT THIS WAY,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

10:47.781 --> 10:49.047
SPIKE: RIGHT THIS WAY.
LEAH: RIGHT OVER HER, FOLKS.

10:49.048 --> 10:50.314
SPIKE:
RIGHT THIS WAY, PLEASE.
THANK YOU.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.417
SORRY, FOLKS.
PORT AUTHORITY.

10:52.419 --> 10:55.720
WE HAVE TO VACATE THIS BOAT.
TECHNICAL ISSUES.

10:55.722 --> 10:56.955
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

10:56.957 --> 10:58.289
RIGHT THIS WAY.

10:59.259 --> 11:01.426
LEAH:
EYES ON SUBJECT -
SEATED BOW, PORT SIDE.

11:01.428 --> 11:02.927
<i> MARIA:</i>
<i> HE LIVES ALONE.</i>

11:02.929 --> 11:04.696
H-HE BARELY COMES OUT.

11:04.698 --> 11:07.232
<i> TODAY, THERE WAS A COUPLE GUYS</i>
<i> IN MOVING UNIFORMS.</i>

11:07.234 --> 11:09.334
THEY WERE BANGING
ON HIS DOOR.

11:09.336 --> 11:11.803
<i> THERE WAS A WOMAN WITH THEM.</i>
<i> SHE WAS CRYING.</i>

11:11.805 --> 11:13.672
<i> I ASKED THEM TO KEEP IT DOWN,</i>
<i> FOR KATIE,</i>

11:13.674 --> 11:17.242
<i> BUT HE NEVER CAME OUT,</i>
<i> SO THEY LEFT.</i>

11:18.412 --> 11:20.245
HE COULD HAVE GONE OUT
OF HIS APARTMENT,

11:20.247 --> 11:22.147
AND UP THE FIRE ESCAPE.

11:22.149 --> 11:24.449
(PANICKING)
IS IT HIM? OH MY-
WHY WOULD HE DO THIS?!

11:24.451 --> 11:26.217
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> MRS. THOMPSON, I'M GONNA HAVE</i>
<i> A POLICE OFFICER</i>

11:26.219 --> 11:27.719
COME AND GET YOU,

11:27.721 --> 11:29.320
BRING YOU DOWN HERE,
ALL RIGHT?

11:29.322 --> 11:31.022
<i> (MARIA SOBS)</i>
<i> YOU HANG TIGHT.</i>

11:31.024 --> 11:32.357
WINNIE,
"HAROLD BEAMER" -

11:32.359 --> 11:33.792
PSYCH HOSPITALS,
CRIMINAL RECORD,

11:33.794 --> 11:35.393
ANYTHING YOU GOT.

11:35.395 --> 11:37.929
EDDIE, WHAT WAS WITH
THE PIANO THING?

11:37.931 --> 11:39.330
IT WAS JUST A HUNCH.

11:39.332 --> 11:40.365
IT LOOKED LIKE HE WAS
PLAYING SCALES

11:40.367 --> 11:41.433
ON THE GUN BARREL.

11:41.435 --> 11:44.936
"SCALES?" REALLY?
HOW'D YOU KNOW THAT?

11:44.938 --> 11:47.405
OH! CLARK PLAYS,
DOESN'T HE?

11:48.341 --> 11:50.075
TURNS OUT THE HUNCH
WAS GOOD.

11:50.077 --> 11:51.843
HAROLD BEAMER,
ADMITTED TO THE PSYCH WARD

11:51.845 --> 11:54.279
AT ST. PATRICK'S HOSPITAL,
2002.

11:54.281 --> 11:55.480
RIGHT THIS WAY, FOLKS!

11:55.482 --> 11:57.399
SPIKE:
THERE'LL BE ANOTHER BOAT SOON.

11:57.400 --> 11:59.317
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> HE'S A FORMER PIANIST WITH</i>
<i> THE TORONTO PHILHARMONIC.</i>

11:59.319 --> 12:01.920
<i> DIAGNOSED: BIPOLAR/</i>
<i> SCHIZOAFFECTIVE DISORDER.</i>

12:01.922 --> 12:03.988
<i> HE'S PRONE TO DELUSIONS</i>
<i> AND MANIA.</i>

12:03.990 --> 12:08.093
(LOUD BUZZ OF CHATTER,
SEAGULLS CRY NEARBY)

12:09.029 --> 12:11.429
<i> MOTHER:</i>
<i> COME ON, HON,</i>
<i> THE MAN'S BEING VERY PATIENT.</i>

12:11.431 --> 12:13.898
SPIKE:
IT'S FINE, IT'S FINE.
RIGHT THIS WAY, COME ON.

12:13.900 --> 12:15.467
MOTHER: OH LOOK!
SPIKE: MA'AM...

12:15.469 --> 12:17.969
HAROLD:
NO! NO!
YOU NEED TO BE QUIET, OKAY?!

12:17.971 --> 12:18.970
(MOTHER GASPS)

12:18.972 --> 12:20.705
LEAH:
SUBJECT IS ARMED.

12:20.706 --> 12:22.439
SPIKE:
'KAY, SIR, SIR,
LOOK AT ME.

12:22.442 --> 12:24.943
YOU DON'T NEED TO USE
THAT GUN, OKAY?

12:24.945 --> 12:27.462
(BABY CRIES)

12:27.463 --> 12:29.980
OH, LOOK WHAT YOU'VE DONE!
OH NO, OH...

12:29.983 --> 12:32.150
ED:
SAM, PORT SIDE.
JULES, TAKE THE DOOR, STAY LOW.

12:32.152 --> 12:33.351
SAM:
WHAT IF HE COMES OUT
BLASTING?

12:33.353 --> 12:35.253
ED:
WHOEVER HAS THE SHOT
TAKES THE SHOT.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.222
<i> ED:</i>
<i> OUR OPTIONS WERE</i>
<i> EXTREMELY LIMITED.</i>

12:37.224 --> 12:38.223
I MADE SURE EACH OF US
WAS READY

12:38.225 --> 12:39.224
TO NEUTRALIZE THE SUBJECT-

12:39.226 --> 12:41.126
TO "NEUTRALIZE"?

12:42.295 --> 12:43.294
TO KILL.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.130
OKAY. GO ON.

12:46.066 --> 12:47.132
SAY IT.

12:48.101 --> 12:49.167
SORRY?

12:49.168 --> 12:50.234
"HOW COULD YOU KILL
A SICK AND DESPERATE MAN?"

12:50.237 --> 12:51.670
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

12:51.671 --> 12:53.104
ACTUALLY, I WASN'T.
I WAS THINKING ABOUT YOU,

12:53.105 --> 12:54.538
I WASN'T THINKING ABOUT
YOUR EDP.

12:54.541 --> 12:55.540
"HAROLD BEAMER."

12:55.542 --> 12:56.908
WE KNEW HIS NAME
BY THEN.

12:56.910 --> 12:58.109
THAT'S INTERESTING.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.260
WHAT?

12:59.261 --> 13:00.410
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> WELL, WHEN YOU STARTED,</i>
<i> HE WAS "THE EDP"</i>

13:00.413 --> 13:01.412
OR "THE SUBJECT."

13:01.414 --> 13:03.081
NOW, HE'S...
HAROLD BEAMER.

13:03.083 --> 13:05.283
ED:
THAT'S THE JOB.
"CONNECT, RESPECT, PROTECT."

13:05.285 --> 13:07.085
THAT INCLUDES EDP'S
LIKE HAROLD BEAMER.

13:07.087 --> 13:08.219
WE WANNA GET THROUGH
TO THEM

13:08.221 --> 13:09.454
SO WE DON'T HAVE
TO NEUTRALIZE THEM.

13:09.456 --> 13:11.289
THERE'S THAT WORD AGAIN.

13:11.291 --> 13:12.924
(TERSE LAUGH)
IT'S NOT MY WORD.

13:12.926 --> 13:14.292
IT'S OFFICIAL
POLICE TERMINOLOGY.

13:14.294 --> 13:15.960
IT MAKES PEOPLE
FEEL BETTER -

13:15.962 --> 13:17.562
THE BRASS, MEDIA,
EVERYBODY.

13:17.564 --> 13:19.264
TRUST ME, YOU SHOOT A GIRL
IN A PUBLIC PLACE-

13:19.266 --> 13:20.398
"A GIRL?"

13:22.035 --> 13:23.168
WHAT?

13:23.170 --> 13:25.403
YOU SAID "GIRL."

13:25.405 --> 13:29.507
A GIRL, A GUY, "SUBJECT."
HAROLD BEAMER.

13:29.509 --> 13:31.442
PEOPLE WANT YOU TO USE
THE MAGIC WORDS

13:31.444 --> 13:33.928
TO PROTECT THEM-

13:33.929 --> 13:36.413
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> THERE'S NO BRASS HERE, ED.</i>
<i> NO MEDIA. JUST ME.</i>

13:36.416 --> 13:37.682
AND I MAY NOT BE A COP,

13:37.683 --> 13:38.949
BUT MY DAD WAS A 20-YEAR VET
ON THE FORCE,

13:38.952 --> 13:41.486
SO YOU DON'T NEED
TO PROTECT ME.

13:45.559 --> 13:46.825
OKAY.

13:50.363 --> 13:53.898
(SIGHS HEAVILY)
THE SITUATION WAS A MESS,

13:54.901 --> 13:57.335
AND IT WAS ABOUT
TO GET A LOT WORSE.

13:57.337 --> 13:58.469
(BABY WAILS)

13:58.471 --> 14:00.138
HAROLD
OH... OH NO.

14:01.474 --> 14:03.474
PLEASE, OKAY,
NO NOISE.

14:03.476 --> 14:05.577
PLEASE JUST KEEP IT DOWN.

14:05.579 --> 14:07.145
PLEASE JUST KEEP IT DOWN.

14:07.147 --> 14:09.380
JULES:
COME ON, LET'S GO.
QUICK!

14:09.382 --> 14:10.982
(BABY WAILS)

14:10.984 --> 14:13.418
HAROLD:
OH, SHE'S UPSET.
IT'S OKAY, SUZY.

14:13.420 --> 14:15.086
BABY'S NAME IS KATIE.

14:15.088 --> 14:16.855
<i> I DON'T KNOW WHO SUZY IS.</i>

14:16.857 --> 14:19.123
NEXT OF KIN IS LISTED
AS JORDANA HAUSER,

14:19.125 --> 14:21.559
<i> SHE'S BEEN NOTIFIED.</i>

14:21.561 --> 14:23.561
SHHHH... SHE'S VERY SENSITIVE,
SHE'S SENSITIVE.

14:23.563 --> 14:24.929
SHE DOESN'T...
SHE DOESN'T LIKE THE NOISE,

14:24.931 --> 14:27.131
AND SHE...
SHE NEEDS TO HEAR THE MUSIC.

14:27.133 --> 14:28.867
<i> I JUST NEED TO...</i>

14:28.869 --> 14:30.401
I NEED...
I NEED TO TURN IT AROUND.

14:30.403 --> 14:32.070
<i> I NEED TO TURN IT AROUND!</i>

14:32.072 --> 14:33.504
(STARTING TO FREAK)
I NEED TO TURN IT AROUND!

14:33.506 --> 14:35.240
SPIKE, JUST KEEP HIM
FOCUSED ON YOU.

14:35.242 --> 14:37.542
OKAY, TALK TO ME,
HOW DO WE TURN IT AROUND?

14:37.544 --> 14:39.277
HAROLD
YOU CAN'T.
ONLY I CAN IF I'M...

14:39.279 --> 14:40.912
HAROLD, HAROLD...

14:41.648 --> 14:43.248
WE DON'T HAVE TO RUSH
THIS THING, OKAY?

14:43.250 --> 14:45.650
WE CAN JUST TALK IT THROUGH.

14:48.421 --> 14:51.122
HOW DO YOU KNOW
MY NAME?

14:51.124 --> 14:53.191
OF COURSE YOU KNOW MY NAME.

14:54.127 --> 14:56.027
YOU KNOW MY BIRTHDAY,
MY BLOOD TYPE,

14:56.029 --> 14:57.328
MY SHOE SIZE -

14:57.330 --> 14:58.429
(EXPLODING)
EVERYTHING!

14:58.431 --> 14:59.564
(BABY SCREAMS)

15:00.500 --> 15:01.599
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT I KNOW THOUGH.

15:01.601 --> 15:03.134
SUZY... OH!

15:04.371 --> 15:07.572
YOU DON'T KNOW...
YOU'RE A LIAR!

15:07.574 --> 15:08.606
(SCREAMING)
YOU'RE A LIAR!

15:09.576 --> 15:11.676
I DON'T HAVE THE SHOT!

15:15.081 --> 15:16.581
SAM:
HAROLD, STOP RIGHT THERE!

15:16.583 --> 15:18.416
(BABY CRIES)

15:18.418 --> 15:20.084
IT'S OKAY...

15:20.086 --> 15:22.453
HAROLD:
OH! SUZY...
IT'S OKAY, SUZY.

15:22.455 --> 15:23.454
ED:
IT'S OKAY.

15:23.456 --> 15:25.023
DADDY'S...
DADDY'S HERE.

15:25.025 --> 15:26.224
<i> ED:</i>
<i> THANK YOU, HAROLD.</i>

15:26.226 --> 15:27.625
THANK YOU FOR THAT.

15:28.561 --> 15:30.061
HAROLD...

15:30.062 --> 15:31.562
HAROLD:
DON'T WORRY,
DADDY'S GOT YOU.

15:31.563 --> 15:33.063
<i> ED: HAROLD! HAROLD!</i>
HAROLD: DADDY'S HERE, SUZY.

15:34.567 --> 15:37.035
HAROLD, YOU DON'T NEED
TO DO THAT.

15:37.037 --> 15:38.102
(BABY WAILS)

15:47.614 --> 15:49.480
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> ED?</i>

15:50.984 --> 15:52.116
<i> ED?</i>

15:53.620 --> 15:54.986
CAN YOU KEEP GOING?

15:55.722 --> 15:57.655
<i> THE BABY,</i>
<i> WAS SHE OKAY?</i>

15:57.657 --> 15:59.724
YOU WANT A HAPPY ENDING.

16:00.961 --> 16:02.093
EVERYBODY DOES.

16:03.496 --> 16:05.630
BUT WHEN THINGS DON'T WORK OUT,
YOU KNOW WHO THEY BLAME?

16:05.632 --> 16:07.966
(BABY'S CRIES ECHO)

16:07.968 --> 16:09.600
I COULD SEE THE BABY,
RIGHT THERE,

16:09.602 --> 16:11.602
BUT THERE WAS NOTHING
THAT I COULD DO ABOUT IT.

16:11.604 --> 16:13.137
(HIGH-PITCHED WAIL)

16:13.139 --> 16:14.138
<i> ED:</i>
<i> WE COULDN'T SHOOT -</i>
<i> HE'D DROP HER.</i>

16:14.140 --> 16:16.274
<i> WE COULDN'T RUSH HIM -</i>

16:16.276 --> 16:17.508
WE HAD TO WAIT
AND SEE WHAT HE'D DO.

16:17.510 --> 16:18.977
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> ED, STATUS?</i>

16:18.979 --> 16:20.095
ED:
IF HE JUMPS,
I'M GOING IN AFTER HIM.

16:20.096 --> 16:21.212
WE NEED THAT POLICE BOAT
HERE NOW.

16:21.214 --> 16:22.547
HAROLD: NO!
ED: HAROLD!

16:22.549 --> 16:24.749
HAROLD:
STAY BACK!
JUST LEAVE US ALONE!

16:24.751 --> 16:27.051
JORDANA:
YOU HAVE TO LET ME THROUGH!
PLEASE! PLEASE! HAROLD?!

16:27.053 --> 16:28.052
CALM DOWN,
MA'AM.

16:28.054 --> 16:29.253
HAROLD?!
CALM DOWN.
WHO ARE YOU?

16:29.255 --> 16:31.522
I'M JORDANA HAUSER.

16:31.524 --> 16:32.746
YEAH.
WHERE IS HE?

16:32.747 --> 16:33.969
JORDANA: WHAT'D HE DO?
PARKER: CALM, CALM...

16:33.970 --> 16:35.192
JORDANA:
THE OFFICER WOULDN'T TELL ME
WHAT HE DID.

16:35.195 --> 16:36.661
CALM DOWN,
ALL RIGHT?

16:36.663 --> 16:38.663
NOW, WE'RE DEALING WITH A VERY
DANGEROUS SITUATION HERE.

16:38.665 --> 16:39.664
HAROLD'S UP THERE,

16:39.666 --> 16:41.766
HE'S IN AN EXTREME
MANIC STATE.

16:41.768 --> 16:44.068
HE TOOK A BABY,
HE CALLS HER SUZY.

16:44.070 --> 16:47.005
SUZY'S HIS DAUGHTER.
SHE'S OUR DAUGHTER.

16:47.007 --> 16:49.207
BUT SHE'S RIGHT THERE.

16:53.279 --> 16:54.278
HAROLD:
STAY BACK!

16:54.280 --> 16:56.781
ED:
OKAY, HAROLD, JUST WAIT.

16:56.783 --> 16:58.116
<i> HAROLD:</i>
<i> NOOOOO!</i>

16:58.118 --> 16:59.751
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> HAROLD, DON'T DO IT.</i>

16:59.753 --> 17:01.319
ED:
HAROLD, NO!
(BABY WAILS)

17:01.321 --> 17:02.420
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHAT'S HAPPENING, ED?</i>

17:02.422 --> 17:04.355
HE'S CLIMBING.
HE'S STILL GOT THE BABY.

17:04.357 --> 17:06.457
SAM, GET UP TO THE NEXT DECK.

17:06.459 --> 17:09.060
(BABY WAILS,
HAROLD GRUNTS WITH EFFORT)

17:18.738 --> 17:20.371
SAM:
HAROLD, HAROLD,
TAKE IT EASY, OKAY?

17:20.373 --> 17:22.740
WE'RE NOT TRYING
TO HURT YOU.

17:22.742 --> 17:24.275
ED:
THERE'S NOWHERE LEFT TO GO,
HAROLD.

17:24.277 --> 17:27.245
<i> JUST TAKE IT EASY.</i>
<i> IT'S OKAY.</i>

17:28.181 --> 17:31.816
NO. YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND...

17:32.752 --> 17:34.218
<i> ED:</i>
<i> HAROLD!</i>

17:35.288 --> 17:36.354
HAROLD.

17:42.062 --> 17:44.362
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> ED, STOP.</i>

17:44.364 --> 17:45.730
(LABORED BREATHING)
NO, I CAN DO THIS.

17:45.732 --> 17:48.099
DR. BELL
I KNOW, I KNOW,
JUST BREATHE.

17:48.101 --> 17:49.100
<i> LOOK AT ME.</i>

17:49.102 --> 17:50.168
<i> ANY NUMBNESS?</i>
<i> DIZZINESS?</i>

17:50.170 --> 17:51.169
I'M NOT HAVING
A HEART ATTACK.

17:51.171 --> 17:54.072
I DON'T THINK
IT'S YOUR HEART.

17:54.074 --> 17:55.640
I THINK WE SHOULD
GO BACK.

17:55.642 --> 17:56.641
START AGAIN.

17:56.643 --> 17:58.810
OKAY, FINE. FINE.

17:58.812 --> 18:00.111
<i> THE SUBJECT HAD STOPPED,</i>

18:00.113 --> 18:01.112
<i> HE WAS UNRESPONSIVE</i>
<i> TO OUR-</i>

18:01.114 --> 18:02.480
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> NO. NOT THERE.</i>

18:02.481 --> 18:03.847
BACK - TO THE START
OF YOUR DAY.

18:03.850 --> 18:05.850
BECAUSE WE GO THROUGH
Y TIME.

18:05.852 --> 18:08.386
FOR THE PAST TWO MONTHS,
ONE WEEK, AND FIVE DAYS,

18:08.388 --> 18:09.787
YOU COME IN,
CRACK SOME JOKES,

18:09.789 --> 18:11.556
YOU TELL ME
I'M NOT COP,

18:11.558 --> 18:13.324
AND THE MOMENT WE GET
TO SOMETHING REAL,

18:13.326 --> 18:15.660
LIKE YOUR MARRIAGE,
YOUR SON, MAY DALTON,

18:15.662 --> 18:16.828
YOU RACE THROUGH
THE SESSION,

18:16.830 --> 18:18.074
AND THEN YOU LEAVE.

18:18.075 --> 18:19.319
ED:
I DON'T NEED TO TALK
ABOUT ALL THAT.

18:19.320 --> 18:20.564
OU'RE HAVING
A PANIC ATTACK, ED.

18:20.567 --> 18:23.701
DR. BELL
NOT IF YOU WALK OUT OF HERE
YOU DON'T.

18:23.703 --> 18:26.137
I'M NOT YOUR SARGE,

18:26.139 --> 18:28.706
BUT I AM A PSYCHOLOGIST
WITH SPECIFIC OBLIGATIONS,

18:28.708 --> 18:30.875
LIKE REPORTING THAT A PATIENT
WHO WORKS WITH THE PUBLIC,

18:30.877 --> 18:32.510
WHO,
IN MY PROFESSIONAL OPINION,

18:32.512 --> 18:33.611
IS NOT FIT FOR DUTY.

18:33.613 --> 18:34.846
"NOT FIT FOR DUTY?"

18:34.848 --> 18:36.998
<i> LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.</i>

18:36.999 --> 18:39.149
I HAVE FACED EVERY BOARD,
EVERY PANEL, AND EVERY TRIAL,

18:39.152 --> 18:40.318
AND I HAVE BEEN CLEARED!

18:40.320 --> 18:42.520
I'M NOT TALKING
ABOUT THAT, ED.

18:42.522 --> 18:45.857
WHERE WERE YOU
WHEN I HAD TO SHOOT MAY DALTON?

18:45.859 --> 18:47.592
I MEAN, WHO ARE YOU
TO JUDGE ME?

18:47.594 --> 18:48.759
NOBODY WAS THERE,

18:48.761 --> 18:49.760
BUT EVERYBODY WANTS
TO JUDGE ME.

18:49.762 --> 18:51.195
WHO'S JUDGING YOU,
ED?

18:51.196 --> 18:52.629
YOU SAID YOURSELF,
YOU WERE "PROTECTING" US.

18:52.632 --> 18:53.698
BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE!

18:53.700 --> 18:54.832
THEN TELL ME.

18:57.403 --> 18:59.303
TELL ME.

18:59.305 --> 19:01.239
YOU WANNA KNOW?
YES.

19:02.175 --> 19:03.241
OKAY.

19:05.478 --> 19:08.913
I WOKE UP THIS MORNING,
IN MY BASEMENT, ALONE...

19:08.915 --> 19:10.698
(ALARM BLARES,
BABY CRIES)

19:10.699 --> 19:12.482
<i> LIKE I'VE DONE EVERY DAY</i>
<i> FOR THE LAST TWO MONTHS </i>

19:12.485 --> 19:14.685
<i> BECAUSE IT'S JUST EASIER</i>
<i> THAT WAY.</i>

19:14.687 --> 19:16.654
CLARK! CLARK!

19:16.656 --> 19:18.556
COME ON, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THAT RIGHT NOW.

19:18.558 --> 19:19.624
COME ON, IT'S OKAY.

19:19.626 --> 19:21.192
SOPHIE:
HE HAS A RECITAL TOMORROW.

19:21.194 --> 19:22.343
A RECITAL?

19:22.344 --> 19:23.493
WHY AM I THE LAST TO KNOW
ABOUT THIS?

19:25.298 --> 19:26.597
SO, NO,
I WOULDN'T SAY

19:26.599 --> 19:28.566
WE'RE REALLY "CONNECTING"
RIGHT NOW.

19:28.568 --> 19:30.368
OKAY. AND WORK?

19:31.604 --> 19:33.404
(LOCKER SLAMS SHUT)

19:33.406 --> 19:35.673
(DEEP BREATHING)

19:37.610 --> 19:38.676
ALL RIGHT...

19:41.714 --> 19:43.681
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT!

19:43.683 --> 19:45.466
I MEAN, IS THAT WHAT
YOU WANNA HEAR -

19:45.467 --> 19:47.250
THAT I'M SLEEPING ALONE?
THAT MY KID WON'T TALK TO ME?

19:47.253 --> 19:48.886
AND DEEP BREATHING
BEFORE FACING YOUR TEAM?

19:48.888 --> 19:50.254
IT'S NOT LIKE
I LET ANYONE SEE THAT.

19:50.256 --> 19:52.890
WHY DON'T YOU?

19:52.891 --> 19:55.525
'CAUSE I'M THEIR TEAM LEADER.
OKAY, I'M THEIR TEAM LEADER.

19:55.528 --> 19:56.961
<i> WHEN WE'RE ON A CALL,</i>

19:56.963 --> 20:00.231
<i> WHEN IT ALL GOES TO HELL,</i>
<i> THEY LOOK TO ME -</i>

20:00.233 --> 20:04.268
<i> TO BE CALM, TO BE IN CONTROL,</i>
<i> TO KEEP THEM ALL SAFE.</i>

20:04.270 --> 20:06.304
<i> THAT'S MY JOB.</i>

20:06.306 --> 20:07.772
NOBODY WANTS TO KNOW
ABOUT THE REST OF IT.

20:07.774 --> 20:09.941
THEY DON'T NEED
TO SEE THAT.

20:09.943 --> 20:11.576
THANK YOU.

20:11.578 --> 20:13.277
(CHUCKLES)
FOR WHAT?

20:13.279 --> 20:15.279
FOR BEING HONEST.

20:20.687 --> 20:23.554
SO... YOU WERE ON
THE FERRY.

20:23.556 --> 20:24.956
THE BABY WAS SAFE?

20:26.893 --> 20:28.459
NO, THE BABY WASN'T SAFE...

20:29.929 --> 20:31.896
<i> THAT WAS THE PROBLEM,</i>

20:31.898 --> 20:33.497
<i> AND IT WAS STILL</i>
<i> THE PRIORITY.</i>

20:33.499 --> 20:35.233
JULES:
MR. BEAMER?

20:35.235 --> 20:37.868
<i> ED:</i>
<i> OFFICER CALLAGHAN TOOK LEAD</i>
<i> ON NEGOTIATION.</i>

20:37.870 --> 20:39.537
HAROLD?

20:39.539 --> 20:40.838
<i> ED:</i>
<i> WE KNOW WOMEN ARE</i>
<i> LESS THREATENING </i>

20:40.840 --> 20:43.441
<i> TO SUBJECTS LIKE HAROLD.</i>

20:44.377 --> 20:45.843
I'M JULES.

20:45.845 --> 20:47.945
I'M HOPING THAT
WE CAN SORT THIS OUT.

20:47.947 --> 20:51.282
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHERE YOU'RE TRYING TO GO?

20:51.284 --> 20:53.985
WE'RE ON THE CENTER ISLAND
FERRY, AREN'T WE?

20:53.987 --> 20:55.653
JULES:
YOU'RE A MUSICIAN?

20:56.589 --> 20:57.922
I SEE THAT YOU'RE DOING SCALES.

20:57.924 --> 21:00.791
DON'T PATRONIZE ME.
WHAT KIND?

21:00.793 --> 21:02.643
I'M SORRY?

21:02.644 --> 21:04.494
HAROLD:
WHAT KIND OF SCALES
WAS I PLAYING?

21:04.497 --> 21:05.463
I DON'T KNOW.

21:05.465 --> 21:06.931
<i> ED:</i>
<i> THEY'RE EXERCISES.</i>

21:06.933 --> 21:09.867
THEY'RE THE UH...
HANON EXERCISES.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.270
HAROLD:
YEAH.

21:16.909 --> 21:20.311
CAN YOU TELL US ABOUT
YOUR MUSIC, HAROLD?

21:20.313 --> 21:23.481
<i> JORDANA</i>
<i> WHEN WE STARTED DATING,</i>
<i> HE WAS ALREADY "ECCENTRIC."</i>

21:23.483 --> 21:24.949
I'D BEEN SECOND FLUTE
LONG ENOUGH

21:24.951 --> 21:27.418
TO KNOW THE GENIUS TYPE.

21:27.420 --> 21:30.421
HE PLAYED CHOPIN BY EAR
AT AGE 11...

21:30.423 --> 21:33.591
AND... THE PHILHARMONIC
AT AGE 21.

21:34.527 --> 21:38.062
WHEN DID HE STOP
JUST BEING "ECCENTRIC"?

21:38.064 --> 21:39.330
UM...

21:40.066 --> 21:42.767
IT WAS AFTER SUZY
WAS BORN.

21:42.769 --> 21:44.935
HE LIVED FOR HER.

21:44.937 --> 21:47.505
HE WOULD SLEEP
NEXT TO HER CRIB,

21:47.507 --> 21:49.373
<i> IN CASE SHE WOKE UP,</i>

21:49.375 --> 21:53.377
AND HE WOULD PLAY MUSIC TO HER
ON THIS LITTLE...

21:54.314 --> 21:57.381
UM, IT WAS A LITTLE TOY PIANO
THAT WE HAD.

21:57.383 --> 21:59.450
SHE WAS JUST
SIX MONTHS OLD,

21:59.452 --> 22:01.719
BUT HE WAS SURE THAT
SHE WAS SMILING, YOU KNOW;

22:01.721 --> 22:04.622
THAT SHE COULD
HEAR THE MUSIC.

22:04.624 --> 22:08.492
I DIDN'T NOTICE THE CHANGE,
AT FIRST.

22:08.494 --> 22:11.329
THAT HE STOPPED GOING
TO REHEARSALS,

22:11.331 --> 22:12.763
AND THEN HE STOPPED
PLAYING CONCERTS.

22:12.765 --> 22:15.466
YOU KNOW, HE WOULD ONLY
PLAY FOR SUZY.

22:15.468 --> 22:18.836
HAROLD:
THE RIDICULOUS ORCHESTRA,
THE PEOPLE LISTENING...

22:18.838 --> 22:21.072
<i> THEY COULDN'T REALLY HEAR.</i>
<i> I MEAN, NOT REALLY.</i>

22:21.074 --> 22:24.375
MY JORDANA COULD HEAR,
BUT... NOT ANYMORE.

22:25.111 --> 22:27.878
SUZY, SHE COULD HEAR!

22:27.880 --> 22:30.381
I WOULD PLAY FOR HER,
AND IT WAS BEAUTIFUL.

22:30.383 --> 22:33.918
<i> JORDANA:</i>
<i> WHEN HE'S LUCID,</i>
<i> HE KNOWS THAT HE NEEDS HELP.</i>

22:33.920 --> 22:36.053
AND THEN HE STARTS
TO TAKE HIS MEDS

22:36.055 --> 22:38.022
AND HE SAYS
HE CAN'T HEAR THE MUSIC,

22:38.024 --> 22:39.924
SO THEN HE STOPS TAKING
HIS MEDS

22:39.926 --> 22:41.359
AND THEN THIS HAPPENS
AND...

22:42.929 --> 22:45.763
YOU KNOW, WE COULDN'T
STAY TOGETHER...

22:45.765 --> 22:47.832
I PAID FOR AN APARTMENT THOUGH,
YOU KNOW,

22:47.834 --> 22:49.533
AND A PIANO.

22:49.535 --> 22:52.002
AND I KNEW IF I PLAYED
AND I PRACTICED,

22:52.004 --> 22:54.138
AND I PLAYED,
AND THEN SHE WOULD HEAR.

22:54.140 --> 22:56.607
<i> MY SUZY WOULD HEAR.</i>

22:56.609 --> 22:59.076
AND THEN ONE DAY,
A MIRACLE -

22:59.078 --> 23:01.479
SHE'S RIGHT NEXT DOOR.

23:01.481 --> 23:04.615
<i> AND I PLAYED,</i>
<i> AND SHE LISTENED.</i>

23:06.052 --> 23:07.852
IT WAS GOOD.

23:07.854 --> 23:10.554
<i> JORDANA</i>
<i> I CALLED HIM A WEEK AGO,</i>
<i> AND HE WAS RAVING.</i>

23:10.556 --> 23:14.792
SOMETHING ABOUT "SUZY,"
AND "THE MUSIC," AND...

23:14.794 --> 23:17.061
HE HADN'T EATEN IN DAYS.

23:17.063 --> 23:19.096
HE NEEDED HELP,
SO I CALLED THE MOVERS

23:19.098 --> 23:20.998
TO TAKE HIS PIANO
TO THE HOSPITAL,

23:21.000 --> 23:22.600
SO THAT HE COULD PLAY.

23:22.602 --> 23:23.667
BUT THEN WHEN WE GOT THERE
THIS MORNING,

23:23.669 --> 23:25.603
HE WOULDN'T EVEN COME OUT
TO SEE US.

23:25.605 --> 23:26.804
AND THEN THE NEIGHBOUR
CAME OUT

23:26.805 --> 23:28.004
AND TOLD YOU THAT
HER BABY WAS SLEEPING.

23:28.007 --> 23:29.640
OH GOD, NO,
IS THAT THE BABY?

23:29.642 --> 23:31.409
DID I DO THIS?

23:31.411 --> 23:33.577
NO, THIS IS NO ONE'S FAULT.

23:33.579 --> 23:35.980
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU COULD JUST SEE HIM,

23:35.982 --> 23:39.950
<i> IF YOU JUST KNEW HIM </i>
<i> THE WAY THAT HE REALLY IS...</i>

23:39.952 --> 23:42.486
<i> THIS IS NOT WHO HE IS.</i>

23:43.523 --> 23:46.157
<i> ED:</i>
<i> HE WAS JUST STARING AT ME.</i>

23:46.159 --> 23:49.427
NOT JULES.
NOT THE BABY.

23:51.097 --> 23:52.596
ME.

23:52.598 --> 23:55.733
WHY DO YOU THINK
HE WAS STARING AT YOU?

23:57.670 --> 23:59.036
IT DIDN'T MATTER.

23:59.038 --> 24:00.738
HE BELIEVED
WHAT HE BELIEVED.

24:00.740 --> 24:03.607
HE POSED A THREAT TO HIMSELF
AND TO OTHERS.

24:03.609 --> 24:04.608
WE HAD NO CHOICE.

24:04.610 --> 24:05.609
(SCREAMING)
LIAR!

24:05.611 --> 24:07.194
ED:
PUT IT DOWN, HAROLD!

24:07.195 --> 24:08.778
I WOULD NEVER HURT HER!
I WOULD NEVER HURT HER!

24:08.781 --> 24:09.847
(GUNSHOT ECHOES)

24:11.017 --> 24:13.851
AND THE SUBJECT
WAS NEUTRALIZED.

24:14.787 --> 24:16.754
<i> IS THAT WHAT</i>
<i> YOU WANTED TO HEAR?</i>

24:16.756 --> 24:19.023
AM I "FIT FOR DUTY" NOW?

24:19.025 --> 24:21.525
DR. BELL:
I'M SORRY, I JUST...

24:22.662 --> 24:23.828
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW THIS MAN

24:23.830 --> 24:25.796
WENT FROM TELLING YOU
ABOUT THE MUSIC,

24:25.798 --> 24:27.731
AND HIS DAUGHTER,
TO POINTING A GUN.

24:27.733 --> 24:30.034
HE WAS MENTALLY ILL.
HE WAS IN A MANIC PHASE.

24:30.036 --> 24:33.003
BUT WHAT HAPPENED IN THE TIME
BETWEEN HIM STARING AT YOU

24:33.005 --> 24:34.805
AND THE SHOT BEING TAKEN?

24:34.807 --> 24:37.675
<i> WHAT HAPPENED TO JULES?</i>
<i> OR THE BABY?</i>

24:37.677 --> 24:38.776
WHAT'RE YOU LEAVING OUT,
ED?

24:38.778 --> 24:40.378
<i> ED:</i>
<i> I TOLD YOU.</i>

24:40.379 --> 24:41.979
THE MAN WAS SHOT.
HE WAS KILLED.

24:41.981 --> 24:43.047
YES.

24:44.650 --> 24:47.818
BUT YOU DIDN'T SHOOT HIM,
DID YOU, ED?

24:47.820 --> 24:49.887
<i> I TOLD YOU </i>
<i> MY DAD WAS A COP.</i>

24:49.889 --> 24:51.878
<i> SO I KNOW THAT,</i>

24:51.879 --> 24:53.868
AFTER A SHOOTING
IN THE LINE OF DUTY,

24:53.869 --> 24:55.858
AN OFFICER MUST TURN EVERYTHING
OVER TO THE SIU AS EVIDENCE -

24:55.862 --> 24:57.862
HIS NOTEBOOK,
HIS GEAR...

24:59.799 --> 25:01.265
HIS UNIFORM.

25:01.267 --> 25:02.867
<i> SO, TELL ME,</i>

25:03.803 --> 25:06.904
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED
ON THE FERRY?

25:16.115 --> 25:20.117
(BABY'S CRIES ECHO,
STEADY BEATING OF A HEART)

25:28.628 --> 25:30.261
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> ED?</i>

25:30.263 --> 25:31.529
<i> ED.</i>

25:33.032 --> 25:34.131
I WANNA HELP YOU,

25:34.133 --> 25:37.535
BUT YOU HAVE TO BE HONEST
WITH ME.

25:37.537 --> 25:39.937
TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED.

25:42.909 --> 25:45.643
HE JUST WOULDN'T STOP
STARING AT ME.

25:45.645 --> 25:47.111
(SEAGULLS' CRIES ECHO)

25:47.113 --> 25:50.080
JULES:
HAROLD, WE'RE RIGHT HERE
IF YOU WANNA TALK.

25:50.082 --> 25:51.982
HAROLD:
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

25:51.984 --> 25:55.152
THE HANON EXERCISES -
HOW... HOW DID YOU KNOW?

25:56.088 --> 25:58.756
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> ED, HIS VOICE IS LOWERED;</i>
<i> HE'S PERSONALIZING.</i>

25:58.758 --> 26:00.824
HE MIGHT BE TRANSITIONING
TO A LUCID PHASE.

26:01.761 --> 26:02.927
ED:
(QUIETLY)
I GOT THE SHOT.

26:02.929 --> 26:05.463
PARKER:
SAM'S COVERING, ED.

26:05.464 --> 26:07.998
IF HAROLD'S REACHING OUT TO YOU,
YOU REACH BACK.

26:09.035 --> 26:11.035
ED:
MY SON PLAYS, HAROLD.

26:11.037 --> 26:12.903
HAROLD:
THE PIANO?

26:12.905 --> 26:14.572
AND THE CELLO.

26:14.574 --> 26:17.641
OH...
THE SOUL OF THE ORCHESTRA.

26:19.211 --> 26:23.347
(HUMS A FEW LOW NOTES
OF CLAIR DE LUNE)

26:27.587 --> 26:28.652
HI, PRINCESS.

26:30.056 --> 26:33.591
(CONTINUES TO HUM
CLAIR DE LUNE)

26:38.030 --> 26:39.263
DO YOU KNOW THAT ONE?

26:39.265 --> 26:42.800
ED:
I DO. THAT'S...
(TRYING TO REMEMBER)

26:42.802 --> 26:45.035
CLAIR... CLAIR UH...

26:45.037 --> 26:46.837
CLAIR DE LUNE.

26:46.839 --> 26:48.305
DEBUSSY.

26:48.307 --> 26:51.241
(WHISPERING)
THAT'S RIGHT, THAT'S RIGHT.

26:51.243 --> 26:55.245
<i> ED:</i>
<i> AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,</i>
<i> HE SEEMED... HAPPY, </i>

26:55.247 --> 26:57.381
<i> AND FOR A SECOND,</i>
<i> SO DID I.</i>

26:57.383 --> 27:00.250
WHY DO YOU THINK
THAT IS?

27:01.253 --> 27:02.653
(SIGHS) IT MADE ME
THINK OF CLARK.

27:05.925 --> 27:07.625
BUT THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

27:07.626 --> 27:09.326
WE HAD TO MOVE FAST
AND GET INTO REALITY TESTING.

27:09.328 --> 27:11.128
FIND AREAS YOU AGREE ON:

27:11.130 --> 27:12.613
"THE SUN IS OUT,
YOU ARE A MAN..."

27:12.614 --> 27:14.097
WE'RE ON A FERRY.
I'M A POLICE OFFICER.

27:14.100 --> 27:16.200
AND THAT'S A BABY AT YOUR FEET,
RIGHT, HAROLD?

27:19.138 --> 27:21.905
HAROLD:
YEAH, YEAH...
IT'S... IT'S MY SUZY.

27:21.907 --> 27:23.307
ED:
OKAY.

27:23.309 --> 27:27.411
HAROLD, CAN I ASK YOU
HOW YOU KNOW THAT'S SUZY?

27:27.413 --> 27:28.679
(BABY WAILS)

27:31.417 --> 27:33.684
(SHORT, ERRATIC BREATHS)

27:37.056 --> 27:39.056
I KNOW, I DON'T...

27:39.058 --> 27:40.324
WAIT. WAIT, STOP!

27:42.061 --> 27:45.195
ED:
NO PROBLEM, HAROLD.
YOU OKAY?

27:45.197 --> 27:46.931
HAROLD:
BETWEEN ME AND YOU,

27:46.932 --> 27:48.666
THERE SEEMS TO BE A LOT OF
PEOPLE WITH GUNS AROUND HERE.

27:48.668 --> 27:51.802
PROBABLY NOT THE BEST PLACE
FOR A BABY, RIGHT?

27:52.805 --> 27:54.838
NOW, I KNOW THAT YOU DON'T
WANNA HURT ANYBODY HERE,

27:54.840 --> 27:57.141
ESPECIALLY NOT THAT BABY.

27:57.143 --> 27:59.143
HAROLD:
LOOK AT THIS.

28:00.279 --> 28:02.713
I DID THIS,
DIDN'T I?

28:02.715 --> 28:04.181
ED:
IT'S OKAY,
THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE -

28:04.183 --> 28:06.316
TO HELP YOU OUT OF IT.

28:06.318 --> 28:08.285
<i> I THOUGHT IT WAS WORKING.</i>

28:08.287 --> 28:10.421
BUT... THEN HE STARED AT ME
AGAIN,

28:11.357 --> 28:12.389
<i> AND THIS TIME...</i>
<i> IT WAS DIFFERENT.</i>

28:12.391 --> 28:14.792
DIFFERENT HOW?

28:14.793 --> 28:17.194
HE DIDN'T SEEM CURIOUS...
OR INTERESTED IN ME.

28:17.196 --> 28:18.962
THIS TIME...

28:18.964 --> 28:20.431
HE LOOKED LIKE HE FINALLY
UNDERSTOOD SOMETHING.

28:22.034 --> 28:23.701
IT WON'T EVER STOP.

28:24.737 --> 28:26.303
I'LL GO AWAY
AND I'LL TAKE THE PILLS,

28:26.305 --> 28:30.274
AND I'LL... I'LL THINK
THAT I'M BETTER, YOU KNOW?

28:30.276 --> 28:33.410
I'LL JUST END UP BACK HERE
ALL OVER AGAIN.

28:33.412 --> 28:35.245
(SHARP EXHALE)
OKAY, HE'S BOTTOMING OUT.

28:35.247 --> 28:37.014
ED, SAM, WATCH FOR A SHIFT
TO SUICIDE.

28:37.016 --> 28:39.016
<i> JULES, IF HIS ATTENTION</i>
<i> IS ON HIMSELF,</i>

28:39.018 --> 28:40.150
<i> YOU GET THE BABY.</i>

28:40.152 --> 28:41.407
ED:
HAROLD, LET ME ASK YOU,

28:41.408 --> 28:42.663
YOU WERE GOING OVER
TO THE ISLAND, RIGHT?

28:42.664 --> 28:43.919
WHAT'S GOING ON THERE?
TALK TO ME.

28:43.923 --> 28:47.224
HAROLD
I CAME TO GET MY PIANO,
THEY WERE...

28:47.226 --> 28:50.761
THEY WERE BANGING ON THE DOOR
AND SUZY WAS UPSET.

28:50.763 --> 28:52.896
I MEAN, SHE DOESN'T KNOW,
SHE'S JUST A BABY.

28:52.898 --> 28:55.999
ALL THE NOISE,
I JUST WANTED IT TO BE QUIET,

28:56.001 --> 28:57.768
SO I COULD HEAR.

28:57.770 --> 28:59.403
THE MUSIC?

28:59.405 --> 29:00.471
YEAH.

29:02.074 --> 29:04.475
WHEN I...
WHEN I HEAR THE MUSIC,

29:04.477 --> 29:07.344
<i> IT TELLS ME THAT THERE'S LOVE</i>
<i> INSIDE ME AND EVERYONE,</i>

29:07.346 --> 29:09.413
AND THAT WE'RE ALL SAFE.

29:10.349 --> 29:12.816
<i> AND THEN I TAKE MY PILLS,</i>

29:12.818 --> 29:16.086
AND I LISTEN TO THE DOCTOR,
AND THERE'S NO MUSIC.

29:16.088 --> 29:17.454
IT'S JUST ME.

29:18.390 --> 29:19.857
AND ALL THE THINGS
THAT I'VE DONE

29:19.858 --> 29:21.325
AND THE PEOPLE
THAT I'VE HURT -

29:21.327 --> 29:23.060
MY JORDANA, MY-MY...

29:24.363 --> 29:26.029
<i> MY SUZY...</i>

29:26.031 --> 29:27.331
HAROLD, I KNOW YOU LOVE
YOUR DAUGHTER,

29:27.333 --> 29:29.233
BUT WHAT HAPPENED
IS IN THE PAST.

29:29.235 --> 29:31.401
<i> BUT I NEED YOU TO DO</i>
<i> THE RIGHT THING NOW.</i>

29:31.403 --> 29:33.337
NO, IT IS NOT.
IT'S...

29:34.273 --> 29:36.073
IT'S IN HERE.

29:36.075 --> 29:38.208
IT'S IN HERE
AND I CAN'T MAKE IT STOP.

29:38.210 --> 29:40.010
I CAN'T!

29:40.012 --> 29:41.111
<i> (BABY WAILS)</i>

29:42.047 --> 29:43.814
I'M SO SORRY...

29:43.816 --> 29:44.882
(BABY WAILS)

29:45.317 --> 29:47.985
I THINK WE SHOULD GO NOW,
SUZY.

29:50.356 --> 29:52.122
ED:
HAROLD...

29:52.124 --> 29:54.424
ARE YOU SURE OF THAT'S-
THAT'S SUZY, HAROLD?

29:54.426 --> 29:56.293
HAROLD: YES!
<i> ED: OKAY.</i>

29:56.295 --> 29:57.928
YES, IT IS.

30:00.399 --> 30:02.099
YOU DON'T THINK I KNOW
MY OWN DAUGHTER?

30:02.101 --> 30:03.433
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

30:03.435 --> 30:04.868
YOU'RE A LIAR!

30:04.870 --> 30:05.869
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> CAREFUL, EDDIE,</i>
<i> HE'S SPLITTING;</i>

30:05.871 --> 30:07.271
HE'S MAKING YOU THE ENEMY.

30:07.273 --> 30:08.438
ED: HAROLD!
HAROLD: LIAR!

30:08.440 --> 30:09.718
ED:
HAROLD, I'M HERE TO HELP YOU!

30:09.719 --> 30:10.997
HAROLD: NO!
ED: LOOK AT ME! TALK TO ME!

30:10.998 --> 30:12.276
HAROLD:
(SCREAMS WITH RAGE)
NO! I WOULDN'T HURT HER!

30:12.278 --> 30:13.655
SAM:
DROP IT!

30:13.656 --> 30:15.033
HAROLD: I WOULD NEVER HURT HER!
ED: PUT THE GUN DOWN!

30:15.034 --> 30:16.411
<i> ED: PUT IT DOWN!</i>
HAROLD: I WOULD NEVER HURT HER!

30:16.415 --> 30:18.148
(EVERYTHING FREEZES)

30:18.150 --> 30:23.287
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> ED? ED, WHERE ARE YOU?</i>

30:23.289 --> 30:26.156
I'M RIGHT THERE...
IN THE MOMENT...

30:28.394 --> 30:31.028
THE MOMENT I KILL SOMEONE.

30:31.030 --> 30:34.464
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> OKAY. DESCRIBE IT FOR ME.</i>

30:34.466 --> 30:37.401
<i> ED:</i>
<i> I USE A FOUR COUNT</i>
<i> BREATHING METHOD</i>

30:37.403 --> 30:41.138
<i> TO KEEP MY HEART RATE</i>
<i> AT 40 TO 50 BEATS PER MINUTE.</i>

30:41.140 --> 30:44.474
<i> I MAINTAIN LIGHT PRESSURE</i>
<i> ON THE TRIGGER OF MY WEAPON.</i>

30:44.476 --> 30:48.378
<i> I AIM FOR THE CENTER MASS,</i>
<i> IN ORDER TO MAKE THE KILL.</i>

30:48.380 --> 30:52.182
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> BUT IT ISN'T THAT SIMPLE,</i>
<i> IS IT?</i>

30:52.184 --> 30:53.517
<i> I READ SOMEWHERE</i>
<i> THAT IN WORLD WAR II,</i>

30:53.519 --> 30:55.385
ONLY 10 OR 20 PERCENT
OF SOLDIERS

30:55.387 --> 30:57.154
ACTUALLY FIRED
AT THE ENEMY.

30:57.156 --> 30:58.488
THE REST AIMED ABOVE,
TO THE SIDE -

30:58.490 --> 31:00.357
ANYWHERE BUT AT THE MAN.

31:00.359 --> 31:03.327
<i> BECAUSE...IT ISN'T EASY,</i>
<i> IS IT,</i>

31:03.329 --> 31:04.962
TO GO AGAINST
THE FUNDAMENTAL INSTINCT

31:04.964 --> 31:07.998
NOT TO KILL
A FELLOW HUMAN BEING.

31:08.000 --> 31:10.334
I MEAN, THAT'S WHY WE TRAIN -
TO BREAK THAT INSTINCT.

31:10.336 --> 31:12.636
SO THAT IN THE MOMENT,
WE DON'T THINK.

31:12.638 --> 31:14.404
<i> IT'S LIKE A SWITCH -</i>
<i> ON OR OFF, BLACK OR WHITE.</i>

31:14.406 --> 31:16.607
"CONNECT, RESPECT, PROTECT."

31:17.543 --> 31:18.609
OR KILL.

31:19.979 --> 31:23.413
<i> IT IS MY JOB NOW.</i>
<i> THIS IS WHAT I MUST DO.</i>

31:23.415 --> 31:24.882
HAROLD:
(SOUNDS DISTORTED)
NO! I WOULD NEVER...

31:24.884 --> 31:26.550
<i> ED:</i>
<i> THE IMMINENT THREAT</i>
<i> IS CLEAR.</i>

31:26.552 --> 31:28.485
<i> THE TARGET IS CLEAR.</i>

31:28.487 --> 31:30.520
<i> I HAVE THE SHOT...</i>

31:30.522 --> 31:33.290
<i> AND I CAN'T DO IT.</i>

31:34.894 --> 31:36.360
<i>(HEAR HAROLD SCREAMING IN RAGE)</i>

31:36.362 --> 31:38.562
THEN IT ALL WENT WRONG.

31:39.899 --> 31:41.899
I DIDN'T TAKE THE SHOT.

31:43.168 --> 31:45.335
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

31:45.337 --> 31:47.404
I DON'T THINK
I CAN DO THIS JOB ANYMORE.

31:58.017 --> 31:59.616
HOW DO I GO BACK NOW?

32:00.586 --> 32:03.086
I MEAN, WHAT DO I TELL THEM?
WHAT DO I TELL MY FAMILY?

32:03.088 --> 32:05.622
WELL, FIRST,
WE NEED TO FINISH.

32:05.624 --> 32:07.491
YOU DIDN'T HEAR ME?
I AM FINISHED.

32:07.493 --> 32:10.494
NO, ED, ON THE FERRY.
FINISH WHAT HAPPENED THERE.

32:10.496 --> 32:13.096
<i> HAROLD:</i>
<i> YOU DON'T THINK I KNOW</i>
<i> MY OWN DAUGHTER?</i>

32:13.098 --> 32:14.564
(BREATHING HARD)
YOU'RE A LIAR!

32:14.566 --> 32:16.033
ED: HAROLD!
HAROLD: LIAR!

32:16.035 --> 32:17.467
<i> ED:</i>
<i> HAROLD, I'M HERE TO HELP YOU!</i>

32:17.469 --> 32:19.303
<i> LOOK AT ME!</i>
<i> TALK TO ME!</i>

32:19.305 --> 32:20.437
NO!

32:20.439 --> 32:22.205
<i> (BABY CRIES)</i>

32:29.982 --> 32:34.451
(LOUD ROARING AS THE SCREAMING
AND CRYING SWIRL)

32:34.453 --> 32:35.485
(LOUD GUNSHOT)

32:43.696 --> 32:45.429
<i> JORDANA:</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENED?!</i>

32:45.431 --> 32:47.431
<i> WHAT'D YOU DO?!</i>

32:47.433 --> 32:49.566
<i> PARKER: (OVER HEADSET)</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENED UP THERE, ED?</i>

32:49.568 --> 32:52.636
<i> EDDIE!</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENED UP THERE?</i>

32:55.341 --> 32:56.406
ED!

32:58.510 --> 32:59.576
ED!

32:59.578 --> 33:02.379
<i>JORDANA: (SCREAMS HYSTERICALLY)</i>
<i> SOMEBODY TELL ME SOMETHING,</i>
<i> PLEASE!</i>

33:02.381 --> 33:04.181
<i> WHAT HAPPENED?!</i>

33:04.183 --> 33:06.616
<i> WHAT'D YOU DO?</i>

33:06.618 --> 33:10.687
<i> OH NO! TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED,</i>
<i> PLEASE, SOMEBODY!</i>

33:10.689 --> 33:12.356
<i> NO, PLEASE!</i>

33:13.759 --> 33:14.758
ED:
(BREATHING HARD)

33:14.760 --> 33:16.593
SAM:
SUBJECT'S NEUTRALIZED.

33:17.529 --> 33:19.062
ED, WHAT'RE YOU DOING?

33:19.064 --> 33:21.131
GOTTA FIX HIM UP;
HIS FAMILY'S DOWN THERE.

33:22.601 --> 33:24.167
HEY.

33:24.169 --> 33:25.569
THEY CAN'T SEE HIM
LIKE THIS.

33:25.571 --> 33:28.538
(QUIETLY) ED,
IT'S A CRIME SCENE.

33:28.540 --> 33:32.442
YOU CAN'T DO ANYTHING
TO HIS BODY, OKAY?

33:38.050 --> 33:40.751
<i> ED:</i>
<i> I COULDN'T STOP...LOOKING.</i>

33:42.154 --> 33:43.320
AT WHAT?

33:44.256 --> 33:45.322
AT THE HOLE...

33:48.794 --> 33:50.694
WHERE HIS HEART USED TO BE...

33:52.498 --> 33:54.664
<i> WHEN HE WAS STILL ALIVE.</i>

33:54.666 --> 33:56.700
<i> STAINTON:</i>
<i> STEP ASIDE.</i>

33:56.702 --> 33:57.801
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHO TOOK THE SHOT?</i>

33:57.803 --> 33:59.269
SAM:
I DID.

33:59.271 --> 34:00.437
STAINTON:
BRADDOCK, YOU'RE SEQUESTERED,

34:00.439 --> 34:01.671
YOU HAVE TO RELINQUISH
YOUR FIREARM.

34:01.673 --> 34:04.775
YOU KNOW THE DRILL,
I'LL TAKE YOU TO SIU.

34:04.777 --> 34:06.677
THE BABY...

34:06.678 --> 34:08.578
JULES:
SHE'S OKAY. SHE'S ON THE DOCK
WITH HER MOM.

34:08.580 --> 34:10.347
SAYS SHE WANTS TO TALK TO YOU,
SAY THANK YOU.

34:10.349 --> 34:11.448
ED:
JORDANA AND THE DAUGHTER?

34:11.450 --> 34:12.449
PARKER:
WHAT HAPPENED, EDDIE?

34:12.450 --> 34:13.449
STAINTON:
PARKER, WHAT'RE YOU DOING?

34:13.452 --> 34:15.552
ED:
I'VE GOTTA GO.

34:15.554 --> 34:17.070
STAINTON
ED, YOU'RE A WITNESS OFFICER;

34:17.071 --> 34:18.587
THE TEAM STAYS
UNTIL BRADDOCK AND I GO.

34:18.590 --> 34:19.823
I DIDN'T TAKE
THE SHOT.

34:19.825 --> 34:21.224
SPIKE:
HOLD UP, BUDDY,
I'LL COME WITH YOU.

34:21.226 --> 34:22.692
ED:
I GOT IT, NO.

34:25.397 --> 34:28.632
(DISTORTED MURMURS,
SIRENS CHIRP)

34:32.271 --> 34:33.804
(JORDANA'S SOBS ECHO)

34:45.184 --> 34:46.817
<i> ED:</i>
<i> I JUST DROVE.</i>

34:46.818 --> 34:48.451
<i> I GOT IN THE TRUCK,</i>
<i> THE BOOKS WERE IN THE TRUCK,</i>

34:48.452 --> 34:50.085
AND I JUST HAD TO GET HERE.
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

34:50.089 --> 34:52.089
I JUST HAD TO GET HERE.

34:53.258 --> 34:56.593
I BLEW THE CALL.
ANOTHER PERSON'S DEAD.

34:58.130 --> 34:59.396
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

34:59.398 --> 35:01.531
OKAY.
YOU BLEW THE CALL...

35:01.533 --> 35:03.266
NOT SURE THAT'S
WHAT I HEARD.

35:03.268 --> 35:04.768
CAN WE DO A LITTLE BIT
OF REALITY TESTING,

35:04.770 --> 35:06.369
SEE WHAT WE AGREE ON,
THE TWO OF US?

35:06.371 --> 35:07.737
ED: YEAH.
DR. BELL: ALL RIGHT.

35:07.739 --> 35:09.673
THE BABY WAS SAVED.

35:11.376 --> 35:12.592
<i> ED:</i>
<i> YEAH.</i>

35:12.593 --> 35:13.809
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> THE PASSENGERS WERE SAVED.</i>

35:13.812 --> 35:16.330
<i> ED:</i>
<i> RIGHT.</i>

35:16.331 --> 35:18.849
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> YOU PROFILED YOUR SUBJECT,</i>
<i> IN ORDER TO NEGOTIATE.</i>

35:18.851 --> 35:21.685
WHEN ALL OTHER OPTIONS
WERE EXHAUSTED,

35:21.687 --> 35:23.720
YOUR TEAMMATE WAS READY.

35:23.722 --> 35:25.622
WHOEVER HAS THE SHOT
TAKES THE SHOT.

35:25.624 --> 35:27.624
(GUNSHOT ECHOES LOUDLY)

35:30.229 --> 35:32.863
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> SO IT ALL WENT</i>
<i> HOW IT WAS MEANT TO,</i>

35:32.865 --> 35:34.331
<i> BASED ON WHAT YOU TELL ME,</i>

35:34.333 --> 35:35.699
AND BASED ON HOW
YOU TRAINED THEM.

35:35.701 --> 35:38.301
NO, NOT THEM -
NOT THEM AT ALL. ME.

35:38.303 --> 35:40.570
IT'S BLACK OR WHITE;
YOU TAKE THE SHOT OR YOU DON'T.

35:40.572 --> 35:41.838
DR. BELL: YOU KILL OR YOU DON'T.
ED: YES!

35:41.840 --> 35:44.141
AND IF YOU KILL,
YOU'RE JUDGED,

35:44.143 --> 35:45.542
YOU'RE BLAMED.

35:45.544 --> 35:47.661
YES.

35:47.662 --> 35:49.779
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> AND IF YOU DON'T KILL,</i>
<i> YOU JUDGE, YOU BLAME...</i>

35:49.781 --> 35:50.847
YOURSELF.

35:52.484 --> 35:56.486
<i> IS THIS REALLY ABOUT WHETHER</i>
<i> OR NOT YOU TOOK THE SHOT?</i>

35:56.488 --> 35:58.288
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

35:58.290 --> 35:59.789
<i> TO HEAR ME TELL YOU</i>
<i> YOU'RE A MONSTER?</i>

35:59.791 --> 36:02.325
<i> OR TO TELL YOU WHY</i>
<i> YOU CAN'T TALK TO YOUR SON?</i>

36:02.327 --> 36:03.560
DR. BELL: WHAT DO YOU WANT, ED?
ED: I DON'T KNOW!

36:03.562 --> 36:04.962
DR. BELL: YES YOU DO.
ED: I DON'T KNOW!

36:04.963 --> 36:06.363
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> YES YOU DO,</i>
<i> AND YOU HAVE TO TELL ME.</i>

36:06.365 --> 36:07.898
YOU HAVE TO SAY IT.

36:09.601 --> 36:10.901
(VOICE CRACKING)
WHAT'S WRONG WITH ME?

36:10.903 --> 36:12.536
WHAT'S WRONG WITH ME?

36:12.538 --> 36:15.505
I SEE THESE PEOPLE -
EVERYONE I EVER...

36:15.507 --> 36:17.057
MAY DALTON?

36:17.058 --> 36:18.608
ED:
I'M UP ON A ROOF,
I SEE HER THROUGH MY SCOPE -

36:18.610 --> 36:20.610
EVERY DAY,
EVERY NIGHT.

36:22.281 --> 36:24.264
<i> LET ME ASK YOU THIS:</i>

36:24.265 --> 36:26.248
DID YOUR FATHER EVER TALK
ABOUT THAT?

36:27.186 --> 36:28.251
NO.

36:29.655 --> 36:31.888
I MEAN, MAYBE THAT'S WHAT
THE DRINKING WAS ABOUT,

36:31.890 --> 36:33.623
THE NIGHTS AWAY...

36:33.625 --> 36:37.260
<i> UNTIL MY SIXTEENTH BIRTHDAY</i>
<i> WHEN HE DIDN'T COME BACK.</i>

36:37.262 --> 36:39.546
(CLEARS THROAT)

36:39.547 --> 36:41.831
I TRY TO LOOK FOR HIM
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE,

36:41.833 --> 36:43.767
BUT, YOU KNOW,
SO FAR...

36:43.769 --> 36:44.968
YOU KNOW, MAYBE ONE DAY
HE'LL COME BACK

36:44.970 --> 36:49.406
AND TELL ME WHAT IT
WAS LIKE FOR HIM.

36:49.408 --> 36:52.509
BUT SO FAR,
HE HASN'T HAD THE COURAGE.

36:52.511 --> 36:54.277
NOT LIKE YOU.

36:54.279 --> 36:55.745
I COULDN'T DO MY JOB.
THAT'S NOT "COURAGE."

36:55.747 --> 36:56.713
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
YOUR JOB, ED.

36:56.715 --> 36:59.249
I'M TALKING ABOUT YOU.

36:59.985 --> 37:01.952
WHY DID YOU COME HERE?

37:01.954 --> 37:03.853
HAROLD SAID HE WAS GOING
TO THE ISLAND TO BE SAFE.

37:03.855 --> 37:05.288
MAYBE THAT'S WHAT
I WAS LOOKING FOR.

37:05.290 --> 37:08.258
NO. HAROLD WAS GOING
TO THE ISLAND TO ESCAPE.

37:08.260 --> 37:11.595
YOU CAME HERE
FOR SOMETHING ELSE.

37:13.865 --> 37:15.765
LET ME SHOW YOU.

37:17.369 --> 37:18.835
COME WITH ME.

37:20.706 --> 37:22.472
(DOOR CLICKS OPEN)

37:30.782 --> 37:32.249
(ED EXHALES HEAVILY)

37:36.521 --> 37:38.588
IT HURTS TO DO YOUR JOB.

37:40.392 --> 37:42.792
IT HURTS TO TAKE A LIFE.

37:42.794 --> 37:45.028
<i> IT HURTS TO BE THE ONE</i>
<i> WHO STANDS ON A ROOFTOP -</i>

37:45.030 --> 37:46.596
<i> OR A BOAT -</i>

37:46.598 --> 37:47.797
AND KILLS.

37:47.799 --> 37:49.833
EVEN WHEN IT'S RIGHT,
IT HURTS.

37:49.835 --> 37:53.503
<i> SO YOU CAN QUIT YOUR JOB,</i>
<i> STOP TALKING TO YOUR SON,</i>

37:53.505 --> 37:56.406
<i> OR RUN AWAY FROM IT ALL</i>
<i> LIKE MY FATHER, OR HAROLD,</i>

37:56.408 --> 37:57.741
BUT NONE OF THAT
IS GONNA HELP YOU FACE

37:57.743 --> 37:59.809
THE ONE THING YOU'RE ACTUALLY
RUNNING AWAY FROM.

37:59.811 --> 38:01.478
(BREATHING HARD)

38:02.414 --> 38:04.581
SO THE QUESTION IS, ED,

38:04.583 --> 38:08.485
CAN YOU ALLOW YOURSELF
TO FEEL THE PAIN?

38:14.760 --> 38:16.459
(GUNSHOT BLASTS)

38:16.461 --> 38:17.527
(BREATHING HARD)

38:17.529 --> 38:19.896
(MULTIPLE GUNSHOTS)

38:21.400 --> 38:22.866
HOW?

38:22.868 --> 38:25.001
HOW DO I FACE THAT?

38:26.805 --> 38:29.406
(MOURNFUL PIANO PIECE PLAYS)

38:36.615 --> 38:38.014
(GUNSHOT BLASTS)

38:42.954 --> 38:45.021
(SOBS)
SHE WAS EIGHTEEN...

38:46.958 --> 38:48.958
SHE WAS EIGHTEEN.

38:48.960 --> 38:50.593
SHE HAD HER WHOLE...

38:50.595 --> 38:51.695
SHE HAD HER WHOLE LIFE
AHEAD OF HER.

38:51.697 --> 38:53.763
I TOOK IT.

38:53.765 --> 38:54.831
I TOOK IT!

38:56.368 --> 38:57.901
(SOBBING)
I TOOK IT...

39:00.772 --> 39:02.772
SHE WAS...
EIGHTEEN YEARS OLD.

39:03.709 --> 39:04.808
SHE HAD HER WHOLE LIFE
AHEAD OF HER

39:04.810 --> 39:06.042
AND I TOOK IT.

39:07.112 --> 39:08.945
HOW CAN I FACE THAT?

39:08.947 --> 39:11.848
HOW CAN MY KID
LOOK ME IN THE EYE?

39:12.784 --> 39:14.884
YOU KNOW WHAT I SEE
WHEN I LOOK IN YOUR EYE?

39:14.886 --> 39:15.952
(SOBBING)

39:15.954 --> 39:17.754
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> I SEE A COP,</i>

39:17.756 --> 39:18.888
A FATHER,

39:18.890 --> 39:20.357
A HERO,

39:20.359 --> 39:21.424
A MAN.

39:22.961 --> 39:26.496
<i> I'D BE WORRIED ABOUT YOU</i>
<i> IF YOU DIDN'T FEEL LIKE THIS.</i>

39:26.498 --> 39:27.797
I'D BE WORRIED ABOUT YOU

39:27.799 --> 39:31.634
IF YOU DIDN'T COME
TO SEE ME TODAY.

39:31.636 --> 39:33.002
<i> BUT I'M NOT.</i>

39:34.973 --> 39:37.807
<i> YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.</i>

39:37.809 --> 39:39.642
JUST REMEMBER, ED,

39:39.644 --> 39:41.544
THE JOB IS BLACK
AND WHITE,

39:41.546 --> 39:43.980
BUT HOW YOU FEEL ISN'T.

39:43.982 --> 39:46.082
THAT'S... THAT'S OKAY?

39:47.018 --> 39:49.819
YEAH... THAT'S OKAY.

39:54.960 --> 39:57.660
I'VE STOOD ON SO MANY
OF THESE ROOFTOPS.

39:57.662 --> 39:59.929
<i> DR. BELL:</i>
<i> YOU WANT YOUR SON</i>
<i> TO LOOK YOU IN THE EYE,</i>

39:59.931 --> 40:02.599
YOU NEED TO TELL HIM
HOW IT IS.

40:04.703 --> 40:07.704
I GOT A FEW PEOPLE
I GOTTA TALK TO.

40:09.141 --> 40:13.810
YEAH, THERE'S A FEW PEOPLE
I THINK I NEED TO TALK TO.

40:16.448 --> 40:19.916
(SOFT, SWEET,
MOURNFUL PIANO MUSIC PLAYS)

40:22.020 --> 40:32.128
¶¶¶

40:32.130 --> 40:37.100
¶¶¶

40:37.102 --> 40:51.981
¶¶¶

40:51.983 --> 41:02.091
¶¶¶

41:02.093 --> 41:07.163
¶¶¶

41:07.165 --> 41:22.111
¶¶¶

41:22.113 --> 41:28.918
¶¶¶

41:28.920 --> 41:30.954
(PIANO MUSIC STOPS
WHEN CLARK STOPS)

41:30.956 --> 41:32.655
SORRY,
I CAN DO THIS LATER.

41:32.657 --> 41:34.257
ED:
NO. IT'S OKAY.

41:34.259 --> 41:35.525
DON'T STOP.

41:38.630 --> 41:39.963
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

41:41.867 --> 41:43.566
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

41:43.568 --> 41:46.636
(CONTINUES PLAYING PIANO PIECE)
